 class Dog {
    String name;
    int age;

    Dog() {                    // default
        this("Puppy", 0); 
    } 
    Dog(String name) {         // overloaded 
        this(name, 1);
    } 
    Dog(String name, int age) { // main ctor
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }
}

Sure ğŸ‘ hereâ€™s the short version:

* `new Dog("Buddy")` â†’ matches the **1-arg constructor**.
* First line inside it is `this(name, 1)` â†’ jumps to the **2-arg constructor**.
* **2-arg constructor runs fully**, sets `name="Buddy"`, `age=1`.
* When it finishes, control returns to the **1-arg constructor**, which then runs its remaining code.
* Final object: `Dog{name="Buddy", age=1}`. âœ…
